Meet Our Team





Our Advisors





Joseph Owenby
Chief Executive Officer
LPL Principal

Jody has been with Financial Development Corporation (FDC), our predecessor firm, since 1988. Working with his mentor, Dr. Kay Shirley, Jody helped build FDC into one of the top independent financial services practices in the country, and in March 2012 he purchased the firm. Following in Kay’s footsteps, Jody is recognized by LPL Financial with the LPL Financial Executive Council Award 2013, 2014 (awarded to the top 0.018% of LPL’s registered representatives, based on production) and the LPL Chairman’s Council 2012, 2015, 2016 (awarded to the top 0.056% of LPL registered representatives, based on production). Each year, he is invited to sit on the American Funds Chairman’s Advisory Council, an honor given to the top 100 registered representatives in the country based on assets under management.
As a University of Georgia business school graduate, Jody holds the CERTIFIED FINANCIAL PLANNER™ designation, as well as series 7, 24 and 63 securities registrations though LPL Financial. He is also licensed for life, accident and sickness insurance, as well as variable insurance products. Jody helps guide his clients through every aspect of their financial lives. LPL Financial, a member of the Financial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA) and the SIPC, is the largest independent broker/dealer in the nation. (As reported by Financial Planning magazine, June 1996-2016, based on total revenue.)
Jody and his wife, Lauren, have been married since 1990, and they have two wonderful sons, Cal and Cade. Having travelled the world earlier in their lives together, they are now focused on enjoying outdoor activities and sports with their boys. Jody is an active volunteer with his sons’ Cub Scout pack and sports teams.






Greg Gerhard
Chief Financial Officer
Chief Operating Officer
LPL Registered Administrative Associate
greg.gerhard@lpl.com

Greg joined Financial Development Systems (FDS) in July 2012, and has been in the financial industry since 1997. Prior to joining FDS, Greg served as the Director of Grantmaker Education & Strategic Partnerships at the Southeastern Council of Foundations, and spent nine years with SunTrust bank working with non-profit clients, primarily family and community foundations. Prior to working with institutional clients, Greg worked with Kay Shirley and Jody Owenby at Financial Development Corporation for five years. He received his B.A. from the State University of NY at Oswego.  Greg currently holds 7, 63 and 65 securities registrations though LPL Financial.
Greg currently serves as a board member on The May P. & Francis L. Abreu Charitable Trust (a private family foundation), W. G. Raoul Foundation (a private foundation) and the ToolBank USA Executive Advisory Board.  He previously served on many local and national committees and boards for organizations such as the Foundation Center Library, Council of Foundations, Grantmakers for Effective Organizations, World Literacy Initiative, Atlanta Tool Bank, Ronald McDonald House Charities and the Georgia Humanities Council.
Greg and his wife Lauren have two amazing sons, Brady & Colin. They reside in Decatur, GA.






Linda (Kinsey) Lang
LPL Registered Administrative Associate
linda.lang@lpl.com

Linda joined Financial Development Systems in 2008. Linda’s primary responsibilities include meeting with our clients, providing exceptional client service and she prepares countless correspondence and reports for advisors and clients alike. She often oversees company projects and is a key member of the leadership team.
Linda retired from BellSouth after a successful 32 year career with her final role being Director of Network Operations. Linda has a passion for learning and holds a B.A Mathematics, MBA, Masters Certification in Project Management and completed the Certification Professional Education Program (CFP © ).  Linda currently holds 6 and 63 securities registrations though LPL Financial.
Linda and her husband Ward enjoy spending their leisure time with their grandchildren and traveling. Linda also finds much pleasure in gardening and is a novice 1st mate alongside Ward on their boat. For better or worse, she is also a Florida Gator fan.






Jim Colbourne
Chief Investment Analyst
LPL Registered Administrative Associate
jim.colbourne@lpl.com 

Jim joined Financial Development Systems in 2015, and has been in the financial services industry for over 20 years. Jim assists our advisor when meeting with clients to provide direction and focus to help pursue their goals. Jim also serves as a key member of the leadership team. He began his career in New York City, managing the Customer Service department and the Margin and Risk department at National Discount Brokers. He returned to Atlanta as a Vice President and manager of branch operations at Smith Barney, where he assisted clients with their financial questions and needs. Most recently, Jim worked with retirement plan fiduciaries and participants, helping to prepare and steer them to a comfortable retirement. Jim currently holds 7, 9, 10, 24, 63 and 65 securities registrations though LPL Financial.  He is also licensed for life, accident and sickness insurance.
Jim was raised in Marietta, Ga., and still resides there with his wife Kimberly and their two children, Katie and William. In his spare time, Jim enjoys playing golf, traveling, attending sporting events, and spending time with his family.




